author: Immanuel Matthew

text:
Hi Akshat, 

I highly appreciate the intent with which you started this channel - to increase financial literacy, while you make this channel a stream of passive income yourself. There's nothing wrong with that. 

However, it's disappointing to see how you've increasingly pivoted to 'clickbait thumbnails' that set unrealistic expectations among young inexperienced investors, that is your audience. Ex. 20,000 in 1 month, 2x returns in 15 days.

You might say that you discuss everything in detail during the full video and encourage responsible financial behaviour. But, you shouldn't resort to the clickbait method to get views, similar to the strategy for any random Youtube video. Money management is also serious. 

These THUMBNAILS need to go, sorry!

text:
Hey Akshat, 

Thaks for all these videos and I am learning a lot.

I am just not quick enough in detailed analysis of a stock to find reasons of dip or rise.
And at times could not judge during a dip if I should wait more or invest now.

A quick guidance on it will help.

Also I have noticed that while sharing information about Bank stocks and their analysis, you do not consider checking (or showing)  Gross and net NPA. Isn't it should be one of the most important factor to decide in which bank we should invest?

This usually shows how that bank is actually working and type of loans given by that bank which turn to NPA...
There must be some reason why that bank stock is that low right now. Investors and daily traders working in this field from several years must be smart. There must be some reason if they are keeping that stock so low.

Please share your thoughts on this.
